Novak Djokovic sealed a semi-final spot and clinched the year-end world No 1 ranking as the Serb defeated Tomas Berdych at the ATP World Tour Finals on Friday.

Djokovic took just 68 minutes to beat Berdych 6-2, 6-2 and finish top of Group A to book a semi-final against Kei Nishikori, which will be played on Saturday afternoon.

The 27-year-old also will now finish the year at the top of the world rankings for the third time in four years.

