Djokovic then won five of the next seven games as he cruised to his 30th consecutive win indoors and then celebrated securing the year-end No 1 ranking with coach Boris Becker and the rest of his camp.

Stan Wawrinka will seal second spot in Group A and a semi-final against compatriot Roger Federer if he can win at least three games against US Open champion Marin Cilic on Friday night. 

 

